    %h2 Inbound Marketing
    %p
      Another terrific source for promotion is Inbound Marketing, which is embedded feature of Androcommerce free plan. Simply put this is a blog injected into your storefront app. With this tool you can talk to your customer and be really creative whilst doing so. For example you may wish to announce world-class event, publish photos of new products, invite enthusiasts for a meat-up, publish fresh reviews, or just throw in some discount coupons. This information will be beamed instantly to all installed storefront apps via Push Notifications. So you will be in touch with your customers who presumably will be flocking after you (their cherished leader and subject matter expert). We are strong believers in Inbound Marketing. Just give it a go!

.row
  .col-xs-12.col-sm-4
    = image_tag "stores_image.png",  class: 'img-responsive img-center img-padding-top'
  .col-xs-12.col-sm-8
    %h2 Use Mobile App Markets
    %p
      The next step is to build up your presence on existing mobile app markets. It is not difficult to create Android Developer account and upload your store-front there. But be aware of pitfalls of globalisation, pay special attention to audience of your app. If you are a local vendor - reduce your audience to town or region. This would rank your app above global competition. If you want to reach out to young and beautiful crowd dazzled by Cupertino, then register Apple Developer Account. We would advise to add DroidBrew representative as your team member. This would give us ability to upload your store-front to App Store. Then again, as per Play Market, go local, conjure local community to your side.

